security first corp  wikipedia security first corp from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search security first corp type private founded rancho santa margarita california united states  founder mark ohare headquarters  santa margarita pky ste  rancho santa margarita ca  key people mark ohare director president and chief executive officer products information assurance and data security spx technology parsedcloud software website httpwwwsecurityfirstcorpcom security first corp is a rancho santa margarita ca information assurance and data security company the company holds over  patents for software defined data security including its secure parser extended spx technology which encrypts and randomly splits data into multiple segments storing them in different locations this technology is also called bitsplitting contents  history  products  media coverage  funding  subsidiaries  references  external links historyedit security first corp was founded in  by mark ohare a  year navy veteran who had served as program executive officer of the us navy aircraft carrier program in  information technology company unisys integrated security firsts secure parser technology into its stealth brand software for windows servers and desktops in june  the company acquired silicon valleybased drc computer corporation drc a developer of acceleration coprocessors security first was reportedly using drcs products for an information security appliance and planned to operate drc as a wholly owned subsidiary in august  ibm announced they were integrating three of security firsts cryptographic technologies into its next generation of chips to increase their security in december  security first released spxsharc for vmwares vcenter server running on vmwares esxi hypervisor in  ibm announced it was using security firsts spxbitfilerips encryption technology to allow ibms pureapplication system virtual pattern deployers to encrypt ondisk data the technology is also licensed by ibm for its cloud data encryption service icdes productsedit security firsts core product is secure parser extended spx technology which encrypts data scrambles it randomly and disperses it to different locations the technology combines aes certified encryption multifactor secret sharing with keyed information dispersal and cryptographic random bitsplitting the solution is compliant with common government and industry data protection standards and security requirements the company offers spx sharc a security suite designed for multisite data protection spx gateway a data protection solution designed to protect data stored across multiple cloud computing service providers a process the company calls cloud spanning and parsedcloud a file transfer application that encrypts splits and transfers data between multiple sites available in free and feebased versions media coverageedit in december  former apple ceo john sculley was interviewed on fox news and called security firsts bitsplitting technology a gamechanger fundingedit in a december  sec filing the company announced it had raised  million from sales of debt and equity from undisclosed investors in an april  sec filing the company announced it had raised an additional  million from sales of debt and equity also from undisclosed investors subsidiariesedit the company operates drc computer corporation as a wholly owned subsidiary referencesedit  a b c security first disruptive innovation redefining data security cioreviewcom retrieved    patents by assignee security first corp justiacom retrieved    a b security first corp game changing technology software defined datacentric security cioreviewcom retrieved    a b making sense of a rollercoaster economy foxnewscom  retrieved    company overview of security first corp bloombergcom retrieved    a b security first corp aims to eliminate customer data risk loyaltycom  retrieved    windows workgroups get encrypted sessions techworldcom  retrieved    a b security first acquires coprocessor firm socaltechcom  retrieved    ibm seeks cloud encryption with security first tieup zdnetcom  retrieved    ibm seeks cloud encryption with security first tieup cloudstrategymagcom  retrieved    ibm encryption pattern for security first spxbitfileripa ibmcom retrieved    staying at the forefront of cybersecurity foxbusinesscom  retrieved    security first corp spx technology advanced data security assured cioreviewcom retrieved    united states securities and exchange commissionform d secgov  retrieved    united states securities and exchange commissionform d secgov  retrieved   external linksedit official website retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlesecurityfirstcorpoldid categories companies based in orange county california establishments in californiainformation governancedata security navigation menu personal tools not logged intalkcontributionscreate accountlog in namespaces article talk variants views read edit view history more search navigation main pagecontentsfeatured contentcurrent eventsrandom articledonate to wikipediawikipedia store interaction helpabout wikipediacommunity portalrecent changescontact page tools what links hererelated changesupload filespecial pagespermanent linkpage informationwikidata itemcite this page printexport create a bookdownload as pdfprintable version languages add links this page was last edited on  march  at  text is available under the creative commons attributionsharealike license additional terms may apply by using this site you agree to the terms of use and privacy policy wikipedia® is a registered trademark of the wikimedia foundation inc a nonprofit organization privacy policy about wikipedia disclaimers contact wikipedia developers cookie statement mobile view security first corp  wikipedia security first corp from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search security first corp type private founded rancho santa margarita california united states  founder mark ohare headquarters  santa margarita pky ste  rancho santa margarita ca  key people mark ohare director president and chief executive officer products information assurance and data security spx technology parsedcloud software website httpwwwsecurityfirstcorpcom security first corp is a rancho santa margarita ca information assurance and data security company the company holds over  patents for software defined data security including its secure parser extended spx technology which encrypts and randomly splits data into multiple segments storing them in different locations this technology is also called bitsplitting contents  history  products  media coverage  funding  subsidiaries  references  external links historyedit security first corp was founded in  by mark ohare a  year navy veteran who had served as program executive officer of the us navy aircraft carrier program in  information technology company unisys integrated security firsts secure parser technology into its stealth brand software for windows servers and desktops in june  the company acquired silicon valleybased drc computer corporation drc a developer of acceleration coprocessors security first was reportedly using drcs products for an information security appliance and planned to operate drc as a wholly owned subsidiary in august  ibm announced they were integrating three of security firsts cryptographic technologies into its next generation of chips to increase their security in december  security first released spxsharc for vmwares vcenter server running on vmwares esxi hypervisor in  ibm announced it was using security firsts spxbitfilerips encryption technology to allow ibms pureapplication system virtual pattern deployers to encrypt ondisk data the technology is also licensed by ibm for its cloud data encryption service icdes productsedit security firsts core product is secure parser extended spx technology which encrypts data scrambles it randomly and disperses it to different locations the technology combines aes certified encryption multifactor secret sharing with keyed information dispersal and cryptographic random bitsplitting the solution is compliant with common government and industry data protection standards and security requirements the company offers spx sharc a security suite designed for multisite data protection spx gateway a data protection solution designed to protect data stored across multiple cloud computing service providers a process the company calls cloud spanning and parsedcloud a file transfer application that encrypts splits and transfers data between multiple sites available in free and feebased versions media coverageedit in december  former apple ceo john sculley was interviewed on fox news and called security firsts bitsplitting technology a gamechanger fundingedit in a december  sec filing the company announced it had raised  million from sales of debt and equity from undisclosed investors in an april  sec filing the company announced it had raised an additional  million from sales of debt and equity also from undisclosed investors subsidiariesedit the company operates drc computer corporation as a wholly owned subsidiary referencesedit  a b c security first disruptive innovation redefining data security cioreviewcom retrieved    patents by assignee security first corp justiacom retrieved    a b security first corp game changing technology software defined datacentric security cioreviewcom retrieved    a b making sense of a rollercoaster economy foxnewscom  retrieved    company overview of security first corp bloombergcom retrieved    a b security first corp aims to eliminate customer data risk loyaltycom  retrieved    windows workgroups get encrypted sessions techworldcom  retrieved    a b security first acquires coprocessor firm socaltechcom  retrieved    ibm seeks cloud encryption with security first tieup zdnetcom  retrieved    ibm seeks cloud encryption with security first tieup cloudstrategymagcom  retrieved    ibm encryption pattern